      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing scripts by a reviewer not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "No independent use-error review performed. Model setup reviewed only by the analyst who constructed it. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that SST k-omega turbulence model and power-law hemolysis model are appropriate for the shear stress and exposure time ranges present in the VAD; comparison to higher-fidelity model or literature benchmark.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected without comparison to LES or DNS reference data in the relevant shear stress regime. Power-law hemolysis model applicability at high-speed VAD conditions not demonstrated. Flagged as major epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients C and alpha, rotor speed, inlet flow rate) characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed across all inputs jointly.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed propagating uncertainty in inlet flow rate and fluid viscosity only. Hemolysis model coefficients C and alpha treated as fixed point estimates despite known inter-study variability of up to 40%. Dominant input drivers not identified because no sensitivity analysis was conducted alongside the Monte Carlo runs; the team notes that sensitivity analysis is planned for a future revision. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Biological variability in red blood cell fragility characterized across donor samples; minimum of 5 independent blood or blood-analog batches used in validation experiments.",
      "rationale": "Single blood analog batch used for all validation experiments. Donor-to-donor RBC fragility variability not characterized. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated that input parameters used in validation experiments (fluid properties, operating conditions) are equivalent to COU input parameters within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted at 25°C; COU specifies 37°C blood temperature. Viscosity correction applied analytically but not experimentally verified. Equivalency of hemolysis model coefficients between blood analog and real blood not established. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    }
